== Potato Wedges ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Trim and discard root end from
@baby lettuce{1} leaves; roughly chop leaves. Halve @tomato{1} lengthwise; thinly
slice crosswise into half-moons. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Spread out @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} on a #plate{}; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, salt, and
pepper.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Crispy Tilapia ==

While potatoes roast, pat @tilapia{11%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season
generously all over with @paprika{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Brush tilapia with @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, then press into seasoned panko
until evenly coated on both sides.

Heat a 1⁄4-inch layer of cooking oil in a large, heavy-bottomed pan{} over
medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles when added
to the pan, add coated tilapia.

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cook until panko is golden and fish is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat if tilapia begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate.

== Lemony Salad ==

Halve and toast @demi-baguette{2}.

Place lettuce and tomato in a large #bowl{}; add a large drizzle of
@olive oil{} and juice from two lemon wedges (four wedges for 4 servings).
Season with salt and pepper; toss to combine.

== Assembly ==

Spread half the @smoky garlic herb sauce{1%ounce} over bottom baguette halves;
fill with crispy tilapia, drizzle with remaining smoky garlic herb sauce, and
top with as much salad as you like. Close to form sandwiches.

Divide sandwiches between plates; serve with potato wedges and any remaining
salad on the side.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.